      "B.TECH. I Semester-2 L T P C EC 201: Digital Systems 3 0 2 4 Unit - 1 6 Hours Digital Systems and Binary Numbers: Digital Systems, Binary Numbers, Number‐Base Conversions, Octal and Hexadecimal Numbers, Complements of Numbers, Signed Binary Numbers, Binary Codes, Binary Storage and Registers, Binary Logic. Unit - 2 14 Hours Boolean Algebra and Logic Gates: Introduction, Basic Definitions, Axiomatic Definition of Boolean Algebra, Basic Theorems and Properties of Boolean Algebra, Boolean Functions, Canonical and Standard Forms, Digital Logic Gates, Integrated Circuits. Gate-Level Minimization: Introduction, The Map Method, Two- and Three-Variable Maps, Four‐Variable K-Map, Product-of-Sums Simplification, Don’t‐Care Conditions, NAND and NOR Implementation, Other Two‐Level Implementations, Exclusive-OR Function Combinational Logic: Introduction, Combinational Circuits, Analysis Procedure, Design Procedure, Binary Adder-Subtractor, Decimal Adder, Binary Multiplier, Magnitude Comparator, Decoders, Encoders, Multiplexers. Unit - 3 14 Hours Synchronous Sequential Logic: Introduction, Sequential Circuits, Storage Elements: Latches, Storage Elements: Flip‐Flops, Analysis of Clocked Sequential Circuits (state equations, state table, state diagram, flip-flop input equations, analysis with D, JK & T flip-flops), State Reduction and Assignment, Design Procedure. Registers and Counters: Registers, Shift Registers (bi-directional & unidirectional shift register) Ripple Counters, Synchronous Counters, Other Counters (Ring, Johnson). Unit-4 8 Hours Memory and Programmable Logic: Introduction, Random-Access Memory, Memory Decoding, Error Detection and Correction (Hamming code, Single-Error correction, Double-Error correction), Read-Only Memory, Programmable Logic Array, Programmable Array Logic, Introduction to Sequential Programmable Devices. Total Contact Time: 42 Hours",
