      "Graph Definition, Graph Representation, Basic Concepts of Finite & Infinite Graphs, Incidence and Degree, Isomorphism, Subgraph, Walk, Path and Circuits, Cliques, Cycles and Loops, Operations on Graphs, Connected Graph, Disconnected Graph and Components, Complete Graph, Regular Graph, Bipartite Graph, Weighted Graphs, Directed and Undirected Graphs, Connectivity of Graphs. Euler’s Graph, Hamiltonian Paths & Circuits, Planar Graphs: Properties, Graph Coloring, Vertex Coloring, Chromatic Polynomials, Edge Coloring, Planar Graph Coloring.",
      "GROUP THEORY 8 Hours",
      "Basic properties of Group, Groupoid, semigroup & monoid, Abelian group, Subgroup, Cosets, Normal subgroup, Lagrange’s theorem, Cyclic group, Permutation group, Homomorphism and Isomorphism of groups, Basic properties, error correction, and detection code.",
      "Tutorials will be based on the coverage of the above topics separately (14 Hours). TOTAL: 42L+14T=56 Hours Recommended Books:",
      "1. “Discrete Mathematics and Its Applications,\" Rosen K.H., McGraw Hill, 6th Ed., 2006. 2. “Discrete Mathematical Structure,\" Kolman B., Busby R.C. & Ross S., Prentice Hall of India Pvt. Ltd, 5th Ed, 2003. 3. “Discrete Mathematical Structure with Applications to Computer Science”, Tremblay J. P. & Manohar R., McGraw Hill, 1999. 4. “Graph theory with applications to Engineering & Computer Science,\" Deo Narsingh, Prentice Hall of India Pvt. Ltd., 2000. 5. “Elements of Discrete Mathematics,\" Liu C.L., McGraw Hill, 2000.",
      "CS 202: ICT Workshop - II 0 0 4 2",
      "Unit – 1: Introduction to Website Development 18 Hours",
      "Introduction of HTML: Elements, attributes, Heading, Paragraphs, Style, Formatting, Anchor,",
      "Image, Audio, Video, Table, list, Forms, Form Input, Form Attributes.",
      "Introduction of CSS: Need for CSS, basic syntax and Structure, selectors, Types of CSS, Properties-",
      "Background, Border, Display, Cursor, Buttons, Font, colour, Hover, Margin, Padding, Opacity",
      "Introduction of JavaScript : Variables, Data types, Comment, Operators, If statements, Switch",
      "statement, Loop, Functions, Array, Strings, Date, Math, Events, Document Object Model(DOM),",
      "Validation.",
      "Unit – 2: Introduction to Node.js/React.js 12 Hours",
      "Introduction to MVC architecture. Introduction to NodeJS - Node Package Manager, REPL",
      "Terminal, Node.js Webserver– Server and Clients, Creating a simple server, Rendering",
      "HTML, Rendering JSON Data, Routing, Event driven programming, MongoDB - Introduction to",
      "NoSQL Databases, Database Commands in Mongodb, CRUD operations, Indexing, Database",
      "operations, ReactJS - Overview of React and its benefits, Setting up a development environment,",
      "Creating and rendering React components, Handling Events, Routing and Navigation.",
      "Unit – 3: Ethical use of GenAI 12 Hours",
      "Core ethical principles of the use of AI tools, risks of unethical use, and best practices for ethical use",
      "of GenAI. Introduction to different GenAI tools: Introduction to image generation model, prompt",
      "engineering tools, Introduction to different training models - supervised learning, unsupervised",
      "learning and language model.",
      "Unit – 4: Introduction to Android APP Development 14 Hours",
      "Layouts, Types of Layouts, Widgets: Edit Text, Button, Toggle Button, Checkbox, Radio Button,",
      "Spinner, List View, AutoComplete Text View, Rating Bar, Date Picker, Time Picker, Progress Bar,",
      "Toast, Alert Dialog, Scroll View, Activity and Intents, Fragments, Menu: Option Menu, Context",
      "Menu, Popup Menu.",
      "Total Contact Time: 56 Hours",
      "1. I. Bayross, “Web -enabled commercial application development using HTML, DHTML,",
      "JavaScript, PERL CGI”, BPB Publications, 2009.",
      "2. D. W. Mercer, A. Kent, S. D. Nowicki, D. Mercer, D. Squier and W. Choi, “Beginning",
      "PHP5”, 1st Edition, Wrox, 2004.",
      "3. S. Holzner, “Complete Reference PHP”, McGraw-Hill Education, 2017.",
      "4. 4. M. Glass, Y. Scouarnec, E. Naramore, G. Mailer, J. Stolz and J. G. Gerner, “Beginning",
      "PHP, Apache, MySQL Web Development”, Wrox, 2004.",
      "5. M. Casciaro and L. Mammino, “Node.js Design Patterns”, 3rd ed., Packt, 2020.",
      "6. S. Stefanov, “React Up and Running: Building Web Applications”, O'Reilly Media, 2016.",
      "7. S. Bradshaw, E. Brazil and K. Chodorow, “MongoDB: The Definitive Guide”, 3rd ed.,",
      "O'Reilly Media, 2019.",
      "8. Cathy O'Neil, “Weapons of Math Destruction”, 2016.",
      "B.Tech.-I, Semester-I L T P C",
      "HS 201: Engineering Arts and Sciences 2 0 0 2",
      "Course Outcomes (CO):",
      "At the end of this course, the students should be able to",
      "● Understand the social, ethical, and cultural role of engineering.",
      "● Explore innovation, design thinking, and creativity in engineering.",
      "● Learn to work across disciplines and communicate effectively.",
      "● Develop a holistic mindset for responsible and future-ready engineering.",
      "Engineering, Society, and Sustainability: 6 Hours",
      "Engineering in the context of global challenges; The co-evolution of technology, policy, and society; Climate resilience and",
      "energy innovation; The social and political responsibilities of engineers; Sustainability, justice, and inclusive development",
      "Historical and Institutional Perspectives on Engineering Practice: 6 hours",
      "The legacy and lessons from historical engineering schools (e.g., École des Mines); The evolution from disciplinary silos to",
      "transdisciplinary teams; Engineering design as a cultural and social practice; The myths, rituals, and critique of innovation",
      "culture; Legal and institutional frameworks shaping engineering outcomes",
      "Creativity, Collaboration, and Design Thinking: 8 Hours",
      "Cognitive diversity and creative collaboration; Emotion, culture, and the “moment of opening” in design; Sources of",
      "innovation: Near vs. distant conceptual inspiration; Divergent and convergent thinking in engineering research; The role of",
      "aesthetics, intuition, and values in the design process",
      "Interdisciplinarity, Ethics, and Future Thinking: 8 Hours",
      "Bridging engineering with social science and humanities; Engineering artifacts and their generative/destructive capacities;",
      "Integrating care ethics in science and technology (e.g., nanotech); Knowledge, skill, and wisdom: Humanistic engineering",
      "education; Anticipating futures: Mobility, technology, and uncertainty",
      "Total: 28 Hours",
      "Recommended Book:",
      "1) Subrahmanian, Eswaran, Toluwalogo Odumosu, and Jeffrey Y. Tsao. “Engineering a better future: Interplay",
      "between engineering, social sciences, and innovation.” Springer Nature, 2018."
    ]
  },
