    "publishedAt": "2024-02-09T08:52:26Z",
    "bullets": [
      "Indian Institute of Information Technology Surat Guidelines for the B.Tech Project and Internship",
      "Introduction",
      "1. All B.Tech final-year students shall carry out major project work of 6-month duration as",
      "mandatory",
      "component",
      "their",
      "course",
      "curriculum",
      "8th",
      "semester.",
      "2. The aim of the final year project is to develop student’s knowledge for solving technical",
      "problems",
      "through",
      "mentored",
      "work",
      "order",
      "produce",
      "competent",
      "and",
      "sound",
      "engineers.",
      "3. Student projects must be original and unique. Similar work or titles, even with minor",
      "differences,",
      "are",
      "not",
      "allowed.",
      "4. Each project activity must be supervised by a faculty member of the concerned",
      "department,",
      "termed",
      "Faculty",
      "Supervisor",
      "There",
      "can",
      "most",
      "two",
      "supervisors",
      "for",
      "the",
      "project,",
      "out",
      "which",
      "least",
      "one",
      "shall",
      "supervisor.",
      "5. Every student is required to prepare documentary proofs of the activities done by",
      "him/her.",
      "evaluation",
      "these",
      "activities",
      "will",
      "done",
      "with",
      "additional",
      "feedback",
      "from",
      "other",
      "supervisors,",
      "any.",
      "student",
      "must",
      "submit",
      "his/her",
      "progress",
      "report",
      "regular",
      "basis.",
      "6. Towards the end of the project, the student should prepare the project report which needs",
      "approved",
      "before",
      "final",
      "submission.",
      "7. Students will be allowed to switch from Institute-Project to External-Internship only",
      "within",
      "first",
      "four",
      "weeks",
      "date",
      "commencement",
      "academic",
      "year",
      "2025-26,",
      "this",
      "1st",
      "Feb",
      "2026.",
      "Guidelines Common Guidelines: 1. Within the first two weeks of commencement of the project, the student shall submit a",
      "proposal",
      "after",
      "consultation",
      "supervisor(s).",
      "should",
      "contain",
      "Identification",
      "Problem",
      "Domain,",
      "Objectives,",
      "Feasibility,",
      "Methodology.",
      "2. The student must maintain a weekly log of his/her work (FORM – 2) and must submit to his/her supervisor weekly. 3. The student must present his/her work to the evaluation panel as and when notified pertaining to the Evaluation Scheme. 4. For successful completion of the project, the student must prepare the project report according to the provided Project-Report Guidelines.",
      "Additional Guidelines for the Institute Project: 1. The student should communicate his/her project work in Scopus/Web of Science",
      "indexed",
      "conferences/journals.",
      "Additional Guidelines for the External Internship: 1. As soon as the student gets the external internship opportunity, he or she must inform the T&P Office regarding the internship details and submit the offer letters to the T&P office. Only after verification from the T&P office, the internship will be finalized. 2. A suitable Faculty Supervisor shall be assigned to each student pursuing an external internship and it is student responsibility to update his progress to the supervisor on a regular basis 3. After joining, the student must submit the FORM–1 (Internship Synopsis) to his Faculty supervisor and T&P Office through the email by keeping his/her External supervisor and HR into cc. A hard copy should be submitted to the T&P office on the student's next campus visit. 4. The Faculty Supervisor may assign additional technical/research/innovative work to the student in case he/she finds the work being provided to the student by the external supervisor is just training work OR is not of the satisfactory level 5. At the end of internship, the student must ensure that his/her “External Supervisor Evaluation of Intern” (FORM–3) report has been submitted by his/her External supervisor to the Faculty supervisor through email. There will be some weightage of this report to student overall evaluation. 6. The student shall ask for ‘Internship Completion Certificate’ to be provided by the organization. 7. The student shall submit a “Student feedback of Internship” (FORM–4) report to T&P office at the time of No-Dues. 8. The student shall try to publish internship work in reputed conferences/journals with due permission/consent from the organization/industry where he/she has undergone the internship.",
      "Evaluation Scheme",
      "The overall evaluation for the institute project involves two presentations, one research publication, and one project report, totalling 800 marks. The overall evaluation for the external project involves two presentations and one project report, totalling 800 marks.",
      "Midsemester Presentation (200 Marks) 1. Shall be held within 10-12 weeks from the starting date of internship. 2. Student presentation should include: Literature Survey, Design Methodology, Planning of Project work, Demonstration of work-done so far, etc.",
      "Endsemester Presentation (Institute-Project students: 200 Marks and other students: 400 Marks) 1. Shall be held at the end of 8",
      "Semester 2. Student presentation should include: Incorporation of suggestions from second/mid-sem presentation, Description of Concepts and Technical Details, Complete Project Demonstration, Conclusion, etc.",
      "Research Publication (Institute-Project students: 200 Marks and other students: NA) 1. The student should communicate his/her project work in a reputed conference/ journal.",
      "Evaluation by the Faculty Supervisor (Institute-Project students: 200 Marks and other students: 100 Marks) 1. The Supervisor should be in regular touch with the student. He/She should evaluate the student based on: Technical Knowledge and Awareness related to the Project, Regularity/Attendance, Quality of the Project Report etc.",
      "Evaluation by the External Supervisor (Non-Institute-Project students: 100 Marks) 1. This should be scaled appropriately from FORM–3. It shall be the responsibility of the student to ensure that their External Supervisor shares this form in a timely manner. In case the response is not received by the due date, the student will receive zero score.",
      "Project-Report Guidelines",
      "1. The project report should be submitted to the Institute as a partial fulfillment for the award of the degree of Bachelor of Technology. 2. It should meet a uniform format detailed in Report Layout that emphasizes readability, concordance with ethical standards and Institute-wide homogeneity. 3. On successful completion of the final presentation, the student is required to submit three hard-bound copies of the final, corrected project report: One copy for the Institute Library, one copy to the faculty supervisor, and one student copy. Additionally, the faculty supervisor is required to submit PDF versions of the final project report and the end-semester presentation to the Library. 4. It will be passed through plagiarism and academic malpractice check, including the use of AI assistance, via softwares like Turnitin. Note that the revision of the BTP report after the final submission is not allowed.",
      "Report Layout Use this template available on Overleaf and organize the report in the following order and print according to the Report Preparation guidelines. 1. Cover Page 2. Inside Color Title Page 3. Color Certificate signed by the Supervisor(s) 4. Internship Certificate 5. Declaration signed by the Candidate 6. Acknowledgements 7. Abstract 8. Table of Contents 9. List of Figures 10. List of Tables",
      "11. Abbreviations/Notations/ Nomenclature (if any) 12. Text of the Report - Chapter 1 - Chapter 2 - … 13. References 14. Appendices (if any) 15. Non-paper materials (if any)",
      "Report Preparation 1. Paper must be white royal executive Bond, 85 gsm of A4 size only. 2. Only the Text of the Report, References, and Appendices may be printed double sided. Each other item should be printed on a single side. 3. Printing Margin: 1.2 inch (left & right) 1.0 inch (Top & Bottom). 4. Font: a. Type: Times New Roman b. Text Size: 12. Justify alignment. c. Chapter Title: 20 Bold d. Topic Title: 16 Bold Underline, left align, (Title Case) e. Sub-topic Title: 14 Bold Underline, left align (Title case). f. In the content page and in the lists of figures and tables, all topics must be written in the title case. 5. Spacing: a. All paragraphs must start without ‘tab’. b. Line Spacing: 1.5 in text c. One line spacing between paragraphs and two lines between chapter title and text d. The new chapters must begin on the right hand side page. e. No blank area at the end of any page except for the last page of the chapter. f. All equations in the middle of line with equation no. at the end of line with small bracket, e.g. (2). g. No dots between equation and equation no. space before and after equation sign. 6. Figures & Tables: a. Must be outside the border & in the center of the whole margin. b. All details in the figure must be clearly readable. c. Write a figure no. at bottom of figure, e.g. (Fig.5.1(a)), followed by the title of figure in the normal case. d. Throughout the report text, the figures must be cited as “Fig.5.1(a)” e. Any figure sourced from a paper or website has to be captioned with ‘Courtesy of’, or give a specific reference number like [1]. f. Write a table number at the top, i.e. (Table 1.1), followed by the title. 7. References: a. Cite references appropriately in text and in figures using [ref. No.] b. All the reference citations must appear in the report text for which they have been refereed.",
      "c. Preferably at least two or three references have to be recent published paper from some reputed national/ international journals, preferably by IEEE. d. Reference List must be written in IEEE Journal/Transaction format. 8. Extra information should be given in Appendices (e.g. datasheets, relevant proofs, charts, etc.)",
      "Form-1 Internship Synopsis",
      "An internship is a unique learning experience that integrates studies with practical work. This agreement is written by the student in consultation with the Faculty Supervisor and External Supervisor. It shall serve to clarify the educational purpose of the internship and to ensure an understanding of the total learning experience among the principal parties involved.",
