      "Bonding in solids: Ionic, Covalent, Metallic, Vander Waal and Hydrogen.",
      "Free-electron theory of metals, Band theory of solids, Semiconductors: Intrinsic & extrinsic, The p-",
      "n junction, p-n junction with an applied voltage, capacitive effects in p-n junction, Hall effect,",
      "Superconductivity: Type I and type II, Meissner effect.",
      "Laser Physics & Fibre Optics 8 Hours",
      "Introduction to Laser, Characteristics of Lasers, Spontaneous and stimulated emissions,",
      "Einstein’scoefficients, Population inversion and lasing action.",
      "Laser systems: Ruby laser, He-Ne Laser, Semiconductor Laser, Advanced lasers, Holography.",
      "Fermat’s principle and Snell’s law-optical fibre, Principle and construction, Acceptance cone,",
      "Numerical aperture, V-Number, Types of fibres,",
      "Fabrication: Double Crucible Technique, Vapour phase Oxidation Process, Fibre optic communication",
      "principle, Fibre optic sensors, Other applications of optical fibres.",
      "Physics of Materials and devices 8 Hours",
      "Introduction to Nanomaterials, Quantum confinement effects, 2-D materials, Nanotubes, Nanowires,",
      "Band gap engineering of nanomaterials for nano-devices, nano-sensors, Materials for organic",
      "electronics, OLEDs, Graphene based FETs.",
      "B.Tech.-I, Semester-I L T P C MS 101: Engineering Mathematics 3 1 0 4",
      "DIFFERENTIAL CALCULUS: 6 HOURS",
      "Review of calculus, Successive Differentiation, standard forms, Leibnitz’s theorem, Power series, Radius of convergence, Taylor's and Maclaurin’s series, Taylor’s theorem, and remainder estimation.",
      "DIFFERENTIAL EQUATION: 10 HOURS",
      "Review of differential equations, exact differential equations, and linear differential equations; Second-order differential equations with constant coefficients; Differential equations with variable coefficients, methods of undetermined coefficients, and variation of parameters. Applications: damped forced oscillations and LCR circuit problems.",
      "MULTIPLE INTEGRALS: 6 HOURS",
      "Evaluation of double integrals: change of order of integration, change of variables between Cartesian and polar coordinates. Evaluation of triple integrals: change of variables between Cartesian and cylindrical and spherical coordinates.",
      "VECTOR CALCULUS: 9 HOURS",
      "Scalar and vector point functions, differential operator, gradient, directional derivative, divergence, curl, and Laplacian operator with their properties, line integral- independence of path, surface and volume integrals.",
      "LINEAR ALGEBRA: 11 HOURS",
      "Elementary row operations, Gauss elimination, Gauss-Jordan method, consistency of linear systems, inverse of a matrix, Eigenvalues and Eigenvectors, Cayley-Hamilton theorem, Vector Spaces, Subspace, Linear Independence, Basis and Ranks, Norms, Angles and Orthogonality, Orthogonal Projections, Least square, Least square data fitting, Constrained least square applications. Tutorials will be based on the coverage of the above topics separately (14 Hours). TOTAL: 42L+14T=56 Hours Recommended Books :",
      "● K. A. Stroud and Dexter J. Booth, Advanced Engineering Mathematics, 6",
      "edition, Red Globe Press. ● Erwin Kreyszig, Advanced Engineering Mathematics, 10",
      "Edition, Wiley. ● Dennis G. Zill, Advanced Engineering Mathematics, 6",
      "Edition, John and Bartlett. ● B. S. Grewal, Higher Engineering Mathematics, 44",
      "Edition, Khanna Publishers. ● Jain and Iyenger, Advanced Engineering Mathematics, Narosa Publications, New Delhi.",
      "AS 102: Fundamentals of Biological Sciences 2 0 0 2",
      "Introduction to Biology 6 Hours",
      "Overview of Biological Sciences, Importance and branches of biology (cell biology, genetics,",
      "microbiology, etc.), Cell Structure and Function, cell theory, evolution, homeostasis, Organelles:",
      "nucleus, mitochondria, endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi apparatus, etc. Structure of biological",
      "membranes, Mechanisms of transport: passive transport (diffusion, osmosis), active transport,",
      "endocytosis, and exocytosis.",
      "Genetics 6 Hours",
      "Overview of Genetics, Mendelian Genetics-Laws of inheritance: dominant and recessive traits, Punnett",
      "square, genetic crosses, Applications to heredity and variation, Molecular Genetics-Structure and",
      "function of DNA and RNA, Protein synthesis: transcription and translation, Genetic mutations and their",
      "effects.",
      "Microbiology and Biochemistry 8 Hours",
      "Introduction to Microorganisms, Classification of microorganisms: bacteria, viruses, fungi, and algae,",
      "Role of microorganisms in the environment and biotechnology, Microbial Growth and Reproduction,",
      "Growth phases, binary fission, and factors affecting microbial growth, Microbial techniques in",
      "biotechnology: fermentation, culturing, and bioreactor usage.",
      "Biomolecules, Carbohydrates, proteins, lipids, and nucleic acids: structure, function, and importance,",
      "Enzymes: mechanism of action, types, and regulation, Metabolism-Overview of metabolic pathways:",
      "glycolysis, Krebs cycle, oxidative phosphorylation, Energy transfer (ATP) in biological systems.",
      "Biotechnology and its Applications 5 Hours",
      "Introduction to Biotechnology, Definition, history, and scope of biotechnology, Tools and techniques",
      "in biotechnology: PCR, cloning, gene editing, Applications of Biotechnology-Medical applications:",
      "gene therapy, recombinant proteins, vaccines, Industrial and agricultural applications: GMOs,",
      "fermentation, biofuels, bioremediation.",
      "Ecology, Environmental Science, Issues and Biosafety regulations",
      "5 Hours",
      "Ecosystem Basics, Components of ecosystems: producers, consumers, decomposers, Energy flow and",
