      "Ethical Issues-Ethical concerns in genetic modification, cloning, and human experimentation, Public",
      "perception and regulation of biotechnology, Biosafety and Regulations- Biosafety levels, lab safety",
      "protocols, and handling genetically modified organisms (GMOs).",
      "Total Contact Time: 30 Hours",
      "Recommended Books 1. \"Molecular Biology of the Cell\" by Bruce Alberts, Alexander Johnson, Julian",
      "Lewis, David Morgan, Martin Raff, Keith Roberts, and Peter Walter. 2. \"Biology\" by Neil A. Campbell",
      "and Jane B. Reece. 3. \"Genetics: A Conceptual Approach\" by Benjamin A. Pierce. 4. \"Genetics\" by",
      "James F. Crow and M. Kimura. 4. \"Principles of Biochemistry\" by David L. Nelson and Michael M.",
      "Cox. 5. \"Biochemistry\" by Jeremy M. Berg, John L. Tymoczko, and Lubert Stryer. 6. \"Microbiology:",
      "An Introduction\" by Gerard J. Tortora, Berdell R. Funke, and Christine L. Case. 7. \"Prescott's",
      "Microbiology\" by Joanne Willey, Linda Sherwood, and Christopher J. Woolverton. 8. \"Principles of",
