      "Total Contact Time: 56 Hours 56 Hours",
      "1. Electronic Principles, Albert Malvino and David J Bates, McGraw Hill (7th Edition)",
      "2. https://www.arduino.cc/",
      "3. http://www.ni.com/en-in/innovations/white-papers/10/pcb-design-fundamentals---main- page.html",
      "4. https://matlabacademy.mathworks.com/en/details/matlab-onramp/gettingstarted",
      "B.TECH. I Semester-I L T P C EC 102: Introduction to Electrical Engineering 3 0 0 3",
      "Recommended Books 1. “Engineering Circuit Analysis”, W. H. Hyat, J. E. Kimmerly, S. M. Durbin, 8thEdition, TMH. 2. “Electric Circuits”, Joseph A Edminister, SI (metric) edition, Schaum’s outline series, McGraw hill, 2nd edition 1983. 3. “Network Analysis”, Van Valkenburg M E, 3rd Edition, PHI, 2002. 4. “Basic electrical engineering”, Kothari and Nagrath, 2nd edition, 2007, Tata McGraw-Hill Education.",
      "Unit 1: Fundamental Laws and Network Analysis Techniques 12 Hours Voltage and Current Laws: Nodes, Paths, Loops, and Branches, Kirchhoff’s Current Law, Kirchhoff’s Voltage Law, The Single Loop Circuit, The Single-Node-Pair Circuit, Series and Parallel Connected Sources, Resistors in Series and Parallel, Voltage and Current Division. Basic Nodal and Mesh Analysis: Nodal Analysis, The Super node, Mesh Analysis, The Super mesh, Nodal vs. Mesh Analysis: A Comparison. Circuit Analysis Techniques: Linearity and Superposition, Source Transformations, Thevenin and Norton Equivalent Circuits, Maximum Power Transfer, Delta-Wye Conversion, Selecting an Approach: A Summary of Various Techniques Unit 2: Fundamentals of RL, RC, and RLC Circuits 12 Hours Basic RL and RC Circuits: The Source-Free RL Circuit, Properties of the Exponential Response, The Source-Free RC Circuit, A More General Perspective, The Unit-Step Function, Driven RL Circuits, Natural and Forced Response, Driven RC Circuits, Predicting the Response of Sequentially Switched Circuits. The RLC Circuit: The Source-Free Parallel Circuit, The Overdamped Parallel RLC Circuit, Critical Damping, The Underdamped Parallel RLC Circuit, The Source-Free Series RLC Circuit, The Complete Response of the RLC Circuit, The Lossless LC Circuit Unit 3: AC Circuit Analysis: Sinusoidal Steady-State and Power Concepts 10 Hours Sinusoidal Steady-State Analysis: Characteristics of Sinusoids, Forced Response to Sinusoidal Functions, The Complex Forcing Function, The Phasor, Impedance and Admittance, Nodal and Mesh Analysis, Phasor Diagrams. AC Circuit Power Analysis: Instantaneous Power, Average Power, Effective Values of Current and Voltage, Apparent Power and Power Factor, Complex Power Unit 4: Frequency Response and Two-Port Network Analysis 8 Hours Frequency Response: Parallel Resonance, Bandwidth and High-Q Circuits, Series Resonance. Two Port Networks: One-Port Networks, Admittance Parameters, Some Equivalent Networks, Impedance Parameters, Hybrid Parameters, Transmission Parameters. Total Contact Time: 42 Hours",
      "B.Tech.-I, Semester-I L T P C",
      "HS 101: Communication Skills and Personality Development 2 0 0 2",
      "Course Outcomes (CO):",
      "At the end of this course, the students should be able to:",
      "● Exhibit effective oral and written communication skills.",
      "● Exhibit confidence, self-awareness, and professional etiquette.",
      "● Prepared for group discussions, interviews, and team collaboration.",
      "● Exhibit leadership skills, empathy, and emotional intelligence.",
      "Fundamentals of Communication: 7 Hours",
      "Introduction to Communication: Process, elements, barriers; Types of Communication: Verbal, non -verbal, formal, informal;",
      "Listening Skills: Types of listening, active listening techniques; Written Communication: Emails, memos, official letters, an d",
      "reports; Body Language & Tone in Communication.",
      "Speaking Skills and Presentation Techniques: 7 hours",
      "Public Speaking: Overcoming stage fear, voice modulation, clarity; Presentation Skills: Structure, visual aids, delivery",
      "techniques; Group Discussions: Format, dos and don'ts, evaluation parameters; Extempore & Debate Practice",
      "Personality Development Essentials: 7 Hours",
      "Self-awareness: SWOT analysis, Johari Window; Time & Stress Management; Goal Setting: SMART goals, personal vision;",
      "Grooming, Etiquette, and First Impressions; Building Confidence and Positive Attitude",
      "Professional Communication & Career Readiness: 7 Hours",
      "Resume Writing and Cover Letters; Interview Skills: Types of interviews, common questions, answering techniques; Workplace",
      "Communication & Etiquette; Leadership & Teamwork: Collaboration, conflict resolution, feedback skills",
      "Recommended Books:",
      "1) Technical Communication: Principles and Practice - Meenakshi Raman & Sangeeta Sharma",
      "2) Communication Skills - Sanjay Kumar & Pushp Lata",
      "3) Personality Development and Soft Skills - Barun K. Mitra",
      "4) Presentation Skills for Students - Joan van Emden & Lucinda Becker"
    ]
