      "B.TECH. II Semester-3 L T P C EC 301: Signals & Systems 3 0 2 4 Unit - 1 8 Hours Introduction: Signals, Systems, and Signal Processing, Classification of Signals, The Concept of Frequency in Continuous-Time and Discrete-Time Signals, Analog-to-Digital and Digital-to-Analog Conversion. Discrete-Time Signals and Systems: Discrete-Time Signals, Discrete-Time Systems, Analysis of Discrete-Time Linear Time-Invariant Systems, Discrete-Time Systems Described by Difference Equations, Implementation of Discrete-Time Systems, Correlation of Discrete-Time Signals. Unit - 2 12 Hours Laplace Transform: Introduction, The Laplace Transform, Region of Convergence, Inverse Laplace Transform, Properties of Laplace Transform, Initial Value Theorem and Final Value Theorem. z-Transform: The z-Transform (Direct & Inverse), Properties of the z-Transform, Rational z- Transforms, Inversion of the z-Transform, Analysis of Linear Time-Invariant Systems in the z-Domain, The One-sided z-Transform. Unit - 3 12 Hours Frequency Analysis of Signals: Frequency Analysis of Continuous-Time Signals, Frequency Analysis of Discrete-Time Signals, Frequency-Domain and Time-Domain Signal Properties, Properties of the Fourier Transform for Discrete-Time Signals. Frequency-Domain Analysis of LTI Systems: Frequency-Domain Characteristics of Linear Time- Invariant Systems, Frequency Response of LTI Systems, Correlation Functions and Spectra at the output of LTI systems, Linear Time-Invariant Systems as Frequency-Selective Filters, Inverse Systems and Deconvolution. Unit - 4 10 Hours Sampling and Reconstruction of Signals: Ideal Sampling and Reconstruction of Continuous-Time Signals, Discrete-Time processing of Continuous-Time Signals, Sampling and Reconstruction of Continuous-Time Bandpass Signals, Sampling of Discrete-Time Signals. Total Contact Time: 42 Hours Recommended Books Text-Book 1. \"Digital Signal Processing: Principle, Algorithms, and Applications\", Prokis John G., Pearson Educations, 4th Ed. Recommended Books 1. \"Signal and Systems”, Oppenheim Alan V., Wilsky Alan S. and Nawab Hamid S., Pearson Educations, 3rd Ed., 2006. 2. \"Linear Systems and Signals\", Lathi B. P., Oxford University Press, 2nd Ed., 2007. 3. \"Introduction to Signal and Systems\", Stuller John Alan, Thomson India Edition, 1st Ed., 2007. 4. \"Fundamental of Signals and Systems\", Roberts M. J. and Govind Sharma, Tata McGraw- Hill, 2nd Ed., 2010.",
