      "3. Jake Vanderplas, Python Data Science Handbook, O’Reilly Media, ISBN: 978-1-491- 91205-8",
      "B.TECH. II Semester-3 L T P C EC 302: Electronic Devices and Circuits 3 0 2 4 Unit-1 12 Hours Diodes: The Ideal Diode, Terminal Characteristics of Junction Diodes, Modeling the Diode Forward Characteristic, Operation in the Reverse Breakdown Region—Zener Diodes, Rectifier Circuits. Transistors: Bipolar Junction Transistors: Device Structure and Physical Operation, Current—Voltage Characteristics. MOS Field Effect Transistors: Device Structure and Physical Operation, Current–Voltage Characteristics. Unit-2 10 Hours Amplifiers: Basic Principles: The Basis for Amplifier Operation, Voltage Amplifier, The Voltage-Transfer Characteristics (VTC), Obtaining Linear Amplification by Biasing the Transistor, The Small-Signal Voltage Gain. Small-Signal Operation and Models: MOSFET small-signal operation and models. Basic Configurations: The Three Basic Configurations, Characterizing Amplifiers, The Common-Source (CS) Amplifier, The Common-Source Amplifier with a Source Resistance, The Common-Gate (CG) Amplifier, The Source Follower, Biasing: The MOSFET Case. Unit-3 10 Hours Introduction, IC Design Philosophy: IC Biasing: The Basic MOSFET Current Source, MOS Current-Steering Circuits, Small-Signal Operation of Current Mirror. The Basic Gain Cell: The CS Amplifier with Current-Source Load, The Intrinsic Gain, Effect of the Output Resistance of the Current-Source Load, Increasing the Gain of the Basic Cell. The Common-Gate Amplifier: The CG Circuit, Output Resistance of a CS Amplifier with a Source Resistance, The Body Effect. The MOS Differential Pair: Operation with a Common-Mode Input Voltage, Operation with a Differential Input Voltage, Large-Signal Operation, Small-Signal Operation, The Differential Amplifier with Current-Source Loads Common-Mode Rejection: The MOS case DC Offset: Input Offset Voltage of the MOS Differential Amplifier. Unit-4 10 Hours Feedback: The General Feedback Structure: Signal-Flow Diagram, The Closed-Loop Gain, The Loop Gain, Summary Some Properties of Negative Feedback: Gain De-sensitivity, Bandwidth Extension, Interference Reduction, Reduction in Nonlinear Distortion. The Feedback Voltage Amplifier: The Series-Shunt Feedback Topology, Examples of Series-Shunt Feedback Amplifiers, Analysis of the Feedback Voltage Amplifier Utilizing the Loop Gain. Other Feedback Amplifier Types: Basic Principles, The Feedback Transconductance Amplifier (Series- Series), The Feedback Trans-Resistance Amplifier (Shunt-Shunt), The Feedback Current Amplifier (Shunt-Series). Total Contact Time: 42 Hours Recommended Books 1. “Engineering Circuit Analysis”, W. H. Hyat, J. E. Kimmerly, S. M. Durbin, 8th Edition, TMH. 2. A. S. Sedra and K. C. Smith, “Microelectronic Circuits”, Oxford University Press, 7th Edition. 3. Thomas L. Floyd, \"Electronic Devices\", Prentice Hall, 9th Edition. 4. Boylestad Robert L. and Nashlesky Louis, “Electronics Device & Circuits and Theory”, PHI, 10th Edition, 2009. 5. Millman Jacob, Halkias Christos C. and Parikh C., “Integrated Electronics”, McGraw-Hill, 2nd Edition, 2009. 6. Schilling Donald L. and Belove E., “Electronics Circuits - Discrete and Integrated”, McGraw-Hill, 3rd Edition, 1989, Reprint 2008. 7. \"Electronic Principles\", Malvin Albert & David J. Bates, Tata McGraw Hill, 7th edition, 2007.",
      "B.TECH. II Semester-3 L T P C EC 303: Sensors & Instrumentation 3 0 2 4",
      "Unit - 1 12 Hours Introduction to Sensors: Definitions and Roles of Sensors and Actuators, Analog and Digital Sensors, Sensor Classification and Selection, Importance of Estimation in Sensing, Sensor Calibration, Innovative Sensor Technologies, Application Scenarios, Human Sensory System, Sensors and Actuators related to Automobiles. Instrumentation Process: Instrumentation Steps, Application Examples, Networked Application, Telemedicine System, Homecare Monitoring System, Water and Air Quality Monitoring etc. Unit - 2 10 Hours Various Sensors and Working: Pressure Sensor, Level Sensor, Flow Sensor, Temperature and Heat Sensor, Distance, Position, Force and Light Sensors, Accelerometers and Inclinometers, Solid State Gyroscopes and Navigation, Magnetic Sensors, Intelligent Sensors and Sensor Networks. Unit - 3 10 Hours Signal Processing in Sensors: Modulation, Filtering, Spectrum Analysis and Correlation, Analog-to- Digital Converters, Amplification and Signal Conditioning. Data Acquisition Systems (DAS): Introduction, Objective, Single and Multi-Channel Channel Data Acquisition Systems, Computer Based DAS, Data Loggers. Unit - 4 10 Hours Advanced Sensing Techniques and Case Studies: Embedded Sensor: Excitation and Interfacing, Wireless Sensors and Actuators for IoT Devices, Biomedical Sensors and their Interfacing, Graphene Based Physical and Chemical Sensors. Total Contact Time: 42 Hours",
      "Basics of Engineering Mathematics, Basics of Signals and Systems, Basics of Signal Processing, Basics of Electrical and Electronics Engineering.",
      "Prerequisite",
      "1.H.S. Kalsi, “Electronic Instrumentation Tata McGraw-Hill, 3rd Ed., 2015. 2.William C. Dunn - Introduction to Instrumentation, Sensors, and Process Control-Artech House Publishers, 2005. 3.Webster, John G., Eren Halit, Measurement, instrumentation, and sensors handbook. Electromagnetic, optical, radiation, chemical, and biomedical measurement-CRC Press, 2014. 4.De Silva, Clarence W - Sensors and actuators _ Engineering System Instrumentation-Taylor & Francis, 2015. 5.Subhas Chandra Mukhopadhyay, Next Generation Sensors and Systems-Springer International Publishing, 2016. 6.Pavel Ripka, Alois Tipek - Modern Sensors Handbook-ISTE USA, 2007."
    ]
