      "B.TECH. II, Semester-IV L T P C EC 401: Control Systems 3 0 2 4",
      "Recommended Books 1. Modern Control Engineering, 5th Edition, by Katsuhiko Ogata. 2. Farid Golnaraghi and Benjamin C Kuo, Automatic Control Systems, 9th Edition, John Wiley and Sons 3. I. J. Nagrath and M. Gopal, Control Systems Engineering, 4th Ed., New age international publishers. 4. D'Azzo and Houpis, Feedback Control Systems, Analysis and Synthesis, 1988. 4. Richard M. Murray and Karl J. Astrom, Feedback Systems: An introduction for Scientists and Engineers, Princeton University Press, 2010. 5. Nagrath I. J. and Gopal M., “Control System Engineering”, 5th Ed, 2008 6. Dorf R. C. and Bishop R. H., “Modern Control Systems” Pearson Education. 2008.",
      "Unit 1 10 Hours Introduction to Control Systems: Introduction, Examples of Control Systems, Closed-Loop Control versus Open-Loop Control, Design and Compensation of Control Systems. Mathematical Modeling of Control Systems: Introduction, Transfer function and Impulse response function, Automatic Control Systems: Introduction to Block Diagrams, Block diagram representation and reduction of a closed loop systems, Signal flow graphs and Mason’s gain formula reduction. Automatic Controllers; Mathematical Modeling of Mechanical Systems and Electrical Systems. Unit 2 12 Hours Transient and Steady-State Response Analyses: Introduction, First order Systems, Second order Systems, Transient Response Analysis; Effects of Integral, and Derivative Control Actions on System Performance, Steady State errors in Unity feedback Control Systems Steady state errors. Introduction to Stability, Routh's stability Criterion. Control Systems Analysis and Design by the Root-Locus Method: Introduction, Root-Locus Plots, Root-Locus Plots of Positive Feedback Systems, Root-Locus Approach to Control System Design. Lead, Lag, Lag-Lead Compensation, Parallel Compensation. Unit 3 10 Hours Control Systems Analysis and Design by the Frequency Response Method Introduction, Bode Diagrams, Polar Plots, Log-Magnitude-versus-Phase Plots, Nyquist Stability Criterion, Stability Analysis, Relative Stability Analysis, Closed-Loop Frequency Response of Unity Feedback Systems, Control Systems Design by Frequency-Response approach. Unit 4 10 Hours Control Systems Analysis and Design in State Space: Modelling in State space: Modern control Theory versus Conventional control theory, Basic definitions, Correlation Between Transfer Functions and State-Space Equations State Space representation of Scalar Differential Equation Systems and Transfer Function Systems, State Transition Matrix, Controllability, Observability, Pole Placement Technique. Total Contact Time: 42 Hours",
      "CS 402: Data Science 3 0 2 4",
