      "B.TECH. III Semester-5 L T P C EC 501: Semiconductor Technology 3 0 0 3 Unit-1 6 Hours Crystal Growth and Wafer Preparation: Introduction, Electronic-Grade Silicon, Czochralski Crystal Growing, Silicon Shaping. Epitaxy: Vapor-Phase Epitaxy, Molecular Beam Epitaxy, Epitaxial Evaluation. Film Deposition: Deposition Processes, Polysilicon, Silicon Dioxide, Silicon Nitride, Plasma-Assisted Depositions, Other Materials Unit-2 8 Hours Oxidation: Growth Mechanism and Kinetics, Oxidation Techniques and Systems, Oxide Properties, Redistribution of Dopants at Interface, Oxidation of Polysilicon, Oxidation-Induced Defects. Diffusion: Models of Diffusion in Solids, Fick's One-Dimensional Diffusion Equations, Atomistic Diffusion Mechanisms, Measurement Techniques, Diffusivities of B, P, As, and Sb, Diffusion in SiO2, Fast Diffusants in Silicon, Diffusion in Polycrystalline Silicon, Diffusion Enhancements and Retardations. Unit-3 8 Hours Ion Implantation: Ion Implant System and Dose Control, Ion Ranges, Disorder Production, Annealing of Implanted Dopant Impurities, Shallow Junctions (As, BF2), Minority-Carrier Effects, Gettering, Effects in VLSI Processing. Lithography: The Lithographic Process, Optical Lithography, Electron Beam Lithography, X-Ray Lithography, Other Lithography Techniques. Unit-4 10 Hours Dry Etching: Pattern Transfer, Low-Pressure Gas Discharges, Plasma-Assisted Etching Techniques, Control of Etch Rate and Selectivity, Control of Edge Profile, Side Effects, Dry Etching Processes for VLSI Technology. Metallization: Methods of Physical Vapor Deposition, Problems Encountered in Metallization, Metallization Failure, Silicides for Gates and Interconnections, Corrosion and Bonding. Unit-5 10 Hours VLSI Process Integration: Basic Considerations for IC Processing, Bipolar IC Technology, NMOS IC Technology, Complementary MOS IC Technology, Miniaturizing VLSI Circuits, Modem IC Fabrication Assembly Techniques and Packaging: Wafer Separation and Sorting, Die Interconnection, Package Types and Fabrication Technologies, Special Package Considerations, Package Application Considerations. Total Contact Time: 42 Hours Recommended Books 1. “VLSI Technology”, S. M. Sze, Mcgraw-Hill. 2. May, Gary S., and Costas J. Spanos. Fundamentals of semiconductor manufacturing and process control. John Wiley & Sons, 2006.",
